.TH CLIP 1 "2026-05-08" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clip \- cross-platform clipboard bridge

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clip
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
\fIcommand\fR | \fBclip\fR
.br
.B clip
\fB--clear\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clip
reads from and writes to the system clipboard with identical behaviour on Windows, macOS, and Linux.
The unified autodetect rule: with no input,
.B clip
pastes; with content on stdin,
.B clip
copies. This holds across every supported environment including interactive TTY, redirected pipe with content, redirected pipe with no content (Git Bash / MSYS / Cygwin where stdin reports redirected even interactively, or an explicit empty pipe like \fB: | clip\fR).
Explicit \fB--copy\fR and \fB--paste\fR flags override autodetection; in scripts where the producer may pipe empty content, use \fB--copy\fR explicitly for deterministic copy behaviour. Use \fBclip --copy < /dev/null\fR to copy an empty string, or \fBclip --clear\fR to empty the clipboard.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-copy
Force copy mode (read stdin to clipboard), overriding autodetect.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-paste
Force paste mode (read clipboard to stdout), overriding autodetect.
.TP
.B \-\-clear
Empty the clipboard.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-raw
Do not strip the trailing newline on paste.
.TP
.B \-\-primary
Target X11/Wayland PRIMARY selection (Linux only; ignored elsewhere). The PRIMARY selection is the X11 middle-click buffer.
.TP
.BR \-\-color ", " \-\-no\-color
Respect \fBNO_COLOR\fR. \fBclip\fR has no coloured output of its own; flags are accepted for suite consistency.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Accepted for suite consistency. \fBclip\fR emits no records, so \fB--json\fR is a no-op.
.TP
.B \-\-describe
Emit structured JSON for AI discoverability.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version and exit.

.SH NEWLINE HANDLING
Copy is byte-preserving. Paste strips exactly one trailing \fB\\n\fR or \fB\\r\\n\fR by default to match \fB$(...)\fR shell-substitution semantics. Pass \fB--raw\fR to disable the strip.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success. Empty clipboard on paste also returns 0 with empty stdout.
.TP
.B 125
Invalid flags, conflicting modes, or invalid UTF-8 input.
.TP
.B 126
Clipboard busy (Windows) or helper binary failed (Linux/macOS).
.TP
.B 127
No clipboard helper found on Linux (install \fBwl-clipboard\fR, \fBxclip\fR, or \fBxsel\fR).

.SH EXAMPLES
Paste:
.RS
.nf
clip
.fi
.RE

Copy:
.RS
.nf
echo hello | clip
.fi
.RE

Clear:
.RS
.nf
clip --clear
.fi
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B WAYLAND_DISPLAY
On Linux, if set, clip prefers \fBwl-copy\fR/\fBwl-paste\fR over X11 helpers.
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disables colour output (clip has no colour itself; flag accepted for suite consistency).

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pbcopy (1),
.BR pbpaste (1),
.BR xclip (1),
.BR xsel (1),
.BR wl-copy (1),
.BR wl-paste (1)
